quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  60,6,"You certainly have an excellent example in them for whoever has hope in Allah and the Last Day. But whoever turns away, then surely Allah ňĻaloneňļ is the Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  60,7,"ňĻIn time,ňļ Allah may bring about goodwill between you and those of them you ňĻnowňļ hold as enemies. For Allah is Most Capable. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  60,8,Allah does not forbid you from dealing kindly and fairly with those who have neither fought nor driven you out of your homes. Surely Allah loves those who are fair
  60,9,"Allah only forbids you from befriending those who have fought you for ňĻyourňļ faith, driven you out of your homes, or supported ňĻothersňļ in doing so. And whoever takes them as friends, then it is they who are the ňĻtrueňļ wrongdoers"
  60,10,"O believers! When the believing women come to you as emigrants,¬†test their intentions‚ÄĒtheir faith¬†is best known to Allah‚ÄĒand if you find them to be believers, then do not send them back to the disbelievers. These ňĻwomenňļ are not lawful ňĻwivesňļ for the disbelievers, nor are the disbelievers lawful ňĻhusbandsňļ for them. ňĻButňļ repay the disbelievers whatever ňĻdowriesňļ they had paid. And there is no blame on you if you marry these ňĻwomenňļ as long as you pay them their dowries. And do not hold on to marriage with polytheistic women.¬†ňĻButňļ demand ňĻrepayment ofňļ whatever ňĻdowriesňļ you had paid, and let the disbelievers do the same. That is the judgment of Allah‚ÄĒHe judges between you. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  60,11,"And if any of your wives desert you to the disbelievers, and later you take spoils from them, then pay those whose wives have gone, the equivalent of whatever ňĻdowryňļ they had paid. And be mindful of Allah, in Whom you believe"